items.name: Monogatari Style | 物语系列 - 物語 (シリーズ ) - Monogatari Series
items.description:
Version V2:

The V2 version has changed the basic model for training, and according to the comments, the anime model of sd1.5 has been used for training. At the same time, better background images were used, totaling 1100 images. The model effect of the V2 version can be presented normally on different checkpoint models, and checkpoint models such as anything, cetus, OrangeMix, ghoatMix, etc. have been tested.

This version has improved image logic, color effects, and stylization, and also has good effects on animated graphics. It is recommended to use it.

Issues to be improved:

Due to the excessive number of training images, the processing of prompt words is relatively sloppy and not handled very meticulously.

2. For wires with the characteristic expression of the Story series, the learning effect of shadow processing is weakened.

版本更新V2：

V2版本更换了训练的基本模型，根据评论的建议，采用sd1.5的anime模型进行训练。同时采用了更好的背景图片，共计1100张图片。V2版本的模型效果可以在不同checkpoint模型上正常呈现，已经测试anything,cetus,OrangeMix,ghoatMix等checkpoint模型。

该版本在图像逻辑，颜色效果，风格化上均有提升，在图生图上也有良好的效果，更建议使用。

待改进的问题：

1. 由于训练图片数量过多，提示词的处理相对马虎，没有非常细致的处理。

2. 对于有物语系列特色表达的电线，阴影处理效果上学习效果减弱。

3. 对人物的表现能力较差，更加强调环境的表达

Introduction（中英文简介）:

This is my first stylized Lora that I've created. The theme is inspired by the Monogatari Series anime style, focusing on landscapes such as streets and cities, and it does not include any characters. I created this Lora because of my love for the Monogatari Series. Civitai was lacking in this particular style of artwork. The Monogatari Series has a distinct and unique style of its own, and I would have felt regretful if there wasn't a Lora in this style. This Lora mainly uses screenshots from the anime adaptations of "Bakemonogatari," "Nisemonogatari," and "Monogatari Series: Second Season." However, it's not yet complete, and I plan to add artworks from other installments of the Monogatari Series in the future. This Lora does not include "Owarimonogatari," as I plan to train a separate Lora for that specific installment.

这是我炼制的第一个风格化lora.主题为 物语系列动画风格，不包含人物，以街道，城市等风景的风格为主。炼制这个Lora的原因是出于对《物语系列》的热爱，而civitai缺少该风格的作品，物语系列风格鲜明有自己的特色，如果没有这种风格的lora我会感到非常遗憾。该Lora的主要使用了《化物语》，《倾物语》，《恋物语》的相关动画截图，还不够完善，后续会继续添加其他物语系列的作品。该lora不包含《伤物语》，《伤物语》的lora我会另外训练。

Suggestions for Use:

base model:

This Lora is trained on the base model YabukiKentaroStyle. If using this Lora, it is recommended to use it in conjunction with YabukiKentaroStyle for optimal results. While other models also produce Lora effects, their performance is relatively inferior.

optimization：

it is recommended to use the DMP++2M SDE optimizer.

Parameters:

0.6-1：The primary alterations focus on lighting and color style, creating a sense of lines

1-1.2：The composition leans towards mid to distant perspectives, featuring strong contrasting colors and enhanced linearity.

above 1.5: Not recommended to use versions above 1.5. While the style becomes more pronounced, the visual coherence of the image deteriorates.

Note:

Terminology such as "utility poles," "traffic lights," and "red street lamps" will have a significant impact on the composition. This is related to the materials I have chosen. This issue will be addressed in future versions.

基本模型：

本lora是在基本模型yabukiKentaroStyle上训练的，如果使用该lora建议与yabukiKentaroStyle配合使用，其他模型也有lora效果但效果相对较差。

优化器：DMP++2M SDE

参数：

0.6-1：主要改变光照和颜色风格，具有线条感。

1.0-1.2：画面相对倾向于中远景，具有强对比色，线条感更加明显

不建议使用1.5及其以上，会导致画面逻辑崩坏，但是风格更鲜明

注意：

电线杆，信号灯，红路灯等词汇会对画面产生较大影响（这与我选用的材料相关，后续版本会解决该问题）

items.name: Jazz Jack Style [Pinchable Cheeks Edition]
items.description:
Makes cheeky chibis. LyCORIS version of previously released LoRA.

How to use
Start with "chibi" and then add whatever else you want. For anything with realism mixed in I recommend putting "3D" and/or "realistic" in negatives and using DPM++ 2M Karras sampler since it leans more towards the drawing style.

Best used on NAI or other models with strong support for more simplistic drawn styles.
At very low strength I saw some signs indicating it could be used to improve general prompting and image quality in other models but it's not something I guarantee or you should expect this LoRA to do.

Misc
Dataset of 50 images trained at 512 resolution trained on NAI.
All images are untouched txt2img, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LyCORS is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist if you want the good stuff.

Embrace the Unseen with the Horror and Beauty Collection

The "Horror And Beauty" collection is a meticulously crafted exploration of the intertwined realms of horror and beauty. Through a fusion of the macabre and the magnificent, this collection brings forth a unique experience that tantalizes the senses and stimulates the imagination.

Usage:

Create your personal masterpiece:

  • Premade Prompts: Utilize HorrorAndBeauty/portraitprompts for an instant creation.

  • Custom Combinations: Mix and match elements from the bank to form your own narrative and visuals.

Examples :

portrait of __bank/emotions__ __bank/creatures__ __bank/actionsposes__, wearing __bank/colors__, __bank/clothings__, in __bank/ambiance__ __bank/settings__, __bank/morbid__, __bank/atmosphere__, __bank/effects__ __bank/objects__

The "Horror And Beauty" collection offers an inspiring blend of horror and elegance, allowing creators to explore new horizons and express their artistry. items.name: Powerpuff Girls Characters and Style LoRA for SD XL
items.description:
This is a character and style LoRA model for SD XL 1.0 for the characters and the style of the Powerpuff Girls, the original and reboot TV animation series.

To use as a character LoRA, apply it to the base model of SD XL 1.0 checkpoints as always, using some high strength value (e.g., 0.9-1.2) with the trigger word ppg and the name of the character you want to see (blossom, bubbles, buttercup or professor utonium.) A single-character use is just as other character LoRA.

This model, however, knows four characters, and it is possible to use more than one character in a single image, though the effect is not stable enough; you will need many iterations before getting a usable result.

To use as a style LoRA, apply it to the base model with some lower strength (0.6-0.8) with the trigger word ppg only (i.e., no Powerpuff Girls character names.)

Some random notes:

  • This model tends to infer flat pink or otherwise unnecessarily pink-ish background.

  • Inferred images may contain some unnecessary flowers or soap bubbles sometimes (for obvious reasons.) I have no good suggestion for the negative prompt words to suppress them. (For example, writing soap bubbles largely mutated Bubbles in my case.) Ideas?

  • Some example images are produced by the AUTOMATIC1111 webui and some others are by ComfyUI. ComfyUI images are refined using the plain refiner model of SD XL 1.0 checkpoints. AUTOMATIC1111 images are not. Also, the seed numbers are incompatible between AUTOMATIC1111 and ComfyUI, as you may already know, and you can't reproduce AUTOMATIC1111 produced example by ComfyUI or vice versa.

  • Although I have no will to restrict uses of this LoRA model in any way, each of the Powerpuff Girls characters appears an intellectual property of the appropriate right holder(s), and you are not allowed to infringe their rights.

  • The training set of this model includes no images of Mojo Jojo. (I'm so sorry about that.)

  • I consider Buttercup is the best among the three girls (and this is not about the LoRA quality.)

Have fun!

items.name: Pushing Everything off the Shelf Into the Pot (PESIP)
items.description:
Hello all, this is a merged model I threw together from some other checkpoints I've picked up around the Civitai pages that I personally liked.

The name comes from the intentions I had creating this model: I was basically just throwing checkpoints I had in my folder together to see what came out.

From my tests with this merge it seems to play well with LoRAs. Plays nice with NSFW as well.

I recommend playing with the sampling method to get optimal results, I've gotten good results with both Euler variants alongside the DPM++ samplers, both Karras and non-Karras variants.

Recommended step count is somewhere from 40 to maybe 60, though I also suggest experimenting with the steps to see what works for you and your chosen sampler. The pictures posted used Clipskip=2 but it seems like the merge looks good with Clipskip=1 as well. It's all up to your preference which one to use.

The VAE is baked into the merge. No external VAE required. (Ignore the VAE recommended pop-up on the side, I don't know how to disable that. I apologize.)

items.name: Asari SDXL
items.description:
This flexible asari LoRA for SDXL is not strongly biased towards the specific Mass Effect character. That made gathering datasets difficult, but it paid off.

Default settings of LoRA weight 0.8 and CFG 5-7 are recommended.

It's trained on 80 images of varying aspect ratios, though more often portrait orientation than landscape. Many had to be upscaled, however.

The captions follow this format: "An asari woman in/wearing ... and ..." and then a list of captions.

  • pale/dark/<blank> blue/purple/teal/green skin

  • faint/black/white/red/yellow eyebrow/full/crest/lip markings

  • comic style, realistic, digital painting, digital drawing

  • fullbody, portrait, halfbody, closeup

Multiple colors in a prompt are always a recipe for disaster, and the flexibility means that a purple asari in a green dress might end up as a green asari in a purple dress.

Limitations:

  • Realism is harder than a drawn/comic style.

  • Skin color below the neck ends mostly right, but sometimes it fails, especially if you're going for realism.

  • Like with bad hands, five or eight crests are common issues.

Settings comparisons for LoRA size and alpha can be found here: https://huggingface.co/vmaple/sdxl-asari-lora/tree/main

SUCKS WITH ANIME MODELS, USE SOME FURRY MODEL INSTEAD
A rare once-in-a-blue-moon gen can occasionally pop up using anime models, but most of them come out looking like soup. I used YiffyMix for most of my gens and they all turned out just fine.

Works well with high Lora prompts: <lora:Lucia:0.9-1>

modelVersions.name: v1.1

items.name: Fantastic_ideas_SDXL 奇思妙想
items.description:
- Model introduction: SDXL model still needs high close-up quality, so a large number of materials from half to face close-up are used;

items.name: Shivangi Khedkar - Indian Actress (SDXL)
items.description:
Shivangi Khedkar is an Indian TV and film actress who has acted in Hindi and Telugu movies.

I have moved entirely to ComfyUI for SDXL image generation, so the flows are embedded in the images.

Let me have your feedback. One request - I'm fine with you down voting something, but have the courtesy to say why. It'll help me either improve the LoRAs or know if it's just your individual opinion.

items.name: Kuroyukihime (Accel World) | 加速世界 黑雪姬 | アクセル・ワールド 黒雪姫

A character LoRA for Kuroyukihime from Accel World in her network avatar outfit. The examples are using LoRA weight=1 and highres fix ESRGAN_4x with denoising strength=0.5.

When applying alternative clothes, please download no_outfit version.

modelVersions.name: v1.0

items.description:
This embedding (textual inversion) has been trained after carefully selecting some images . All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!.

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Connie Sellecca (born Concetta Sellecchia; May 25, 1955) is an American actress, producer, and former model, best known for her roles on the television series Flying High, The Greatest American Hero, and Hotel, for which she was nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Television Series Drama in 1987.

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.
